---
description: Disallow close X buttons in mobile modals and sheets
alwaysApply: true
---

# Mobile Modals Without Close Cross

- In the mobile app, do not add header `X` / close-cross buttons to modals, sheets, or rating dialogs.
- Prefer dismiss via backdrop tap, swipe/gesture if supported, or footer actions like `Cancel`, `Close`, `OK`, `Done`, or `Submit`.
- `AppBottomSheet` should not expose a header close-accessory API for an `X` button.
- If a modal needs an explicit dismissal control, put it in the footer using the shared action buttons, not in the title row.

## Examples

```tsx
// Good
<AppBottomSheet
  open={open}
  onClose={onClose}
  title="Rate this club"
  footer={<AppInfoFooter label="Close" onPress={onClose} />}
/>

// Bad
<AppBottomSheet
  open={open}
  onClose={onClose}
  title="Rate this club"
  titleAccessory={<Feather name="x" size={20} />}
/>
```
